{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Mrk|15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","chapter":15,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":1,"text":"As soon as it was morning, having held a meeting with the elders, scribes, and the whole Sanhedrin, the chief priests tied Jesus up, led him away, and handed him over to Pilate.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":2,"text":"So Pilate asked him, “Are you the king of the Jews?” He answered him, “You say so.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":3,"text":"And the chief priests accused him of many things.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":4,"text":"Pilate questioned him again, “Aren’t you going to answer? Look how many things they are accusing you of!”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":5,"text":"But Jesus still did not answer, and so Pilate was amazed.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":6,"text":"At the festival Pilate used to release for the people a prisoner whom they requested.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":7,"text":"There was one named Barabbas, who was in prison with rebels who had committed murder during the rebellion.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":8,"text":"The crowd came up and began to ask Pilate to do for them as was his custom.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":9,"text":"Pilate answered them, “Do you want me to release the king of the Jews for you?”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":10,"text":"For he knew it was because of envy that the chief priests had handed him over.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":11,"text":"But the chief priests stirred up the crowd so that he would release Barabbas to them instead.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":12,"text":"Pilate asked them again, “Then what do you want me to do with the one you call the king of the Jews?”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":13,"text":"Again they shouted, “Crucify him!”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":14,"text":"Pilate said to them, “Why? What has he done wrong?” But they shouted all the more, “Crucify him!”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":15,"text":"Wanting to satisfy the crowd, Pilate released Barabbas to them; and after having Jesus flogged, he handed him over to be crucified.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":16,"text":"The soldiers led him away into the palace (that is, the governor’s residence ) and called the whole company together.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":17,"text":"They dressed him in a purple robe, twisted together a crown of thorns, and put it on him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":18,"text":"And they began to salute him, “Hail, king of the Jews!”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":19,"text":"They were hitting him on the head with a stick and spitting on him. Getting down on their knees, they were paying him homage.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":20,"text":"After they had mocked him, they stripped him of the purple robe and put his clothes on him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":21,"text":"They forced a man coming in from the country, who was passing by, to carry Jesus’s cross. He was Simon of Cyrene, the father of Alexander and Rufus.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":22,"text":"They brought Jesus to the place called Golgotha (which means Place of the Skull ).","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":23,"text":"They tried to give him wine mixed with myrrh, but he did not take it.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:24","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":24,"text":"Then they crucified him and divided his clothes, casting lots for them to decide what each would get.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:25","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":25,"text":"Now it was nine in the morning when they crucified him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:26","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":26,"text":"The inscription of the charge written against him was: The King of the Jews.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:27","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":27,"text":"They crucified two criminals with him, one on his right and one on his left.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:29","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":29,"text":"Those who passed by were yelling insults at him, shaking their heads, and saying, “Ha! The one who would destroy the temple and rebuild it in three days,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:30","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":30,"text":"save yourself by coming down from the cross!”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:31","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":31,"text":"In the same way, the chief priests with the scribes were mocking him among themselves and saying, “He saved others, but he cannot save himself!","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:32","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":32,"text":"Let the Messiah, the King of Israel, come down now from the cross, so that we may see and believe.” Even those who were crucified with him taunted him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:33","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":33,"text":"When it was noon, darkness came over the whole land until three in the afternoon.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:34","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":34,"text":"And at three Jesus cried out with a loud voice, “Eloi, Eloi, lemá sabachtháni?” which is translated, “My God, my God, why have you abandoned me?”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:35","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":35,"text":"When some of those standing there heard this, they said, “See, he’s calling for Elijah.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:36","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":36,"text":"Someone ran and filled a sponge with sour wine, fixed it on a stick, offered him a drink, and said, “Let’s see if Elijah comes to take him down.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:37","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":37,"text":"Jesus let out a loud cry and breathed his last.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:38","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":38,"text":"Then the curtain of the temple was torn in two from top to bottom.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:39","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":39,"text":"When the centurion, who was standing opposite him, saw the way he breathed his last, he said, “Truly this man was the Son of God!”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:40","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":40,"text":"There were also women watching from a distance. Among them were Mary Magdalene, Mary the mother of James the younger and of Joses, and Salome.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:41","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":41,"text":"In Galilee these women followed him and took care of him. Many other women had come up with him to Jerusalem.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:42","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":42,"text":"When it was already evening, because it was the day of preparation (that is, the day before the Sabbath),","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:43","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":43,"text":"Joseph of Arimathea, a prominent member of the Sanhedrin who was himself looking forward to the kingdom of God, came and boldly went to Pilate and asked for Jesus’s body.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:44","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":44,"text":"Pilate was surprised that he was already dead. Summoning the centurion, he asked him whether he had already died.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:45","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":45,"text":"When he found out from the centurion, he gave the corpse to Joseph.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:46","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":46,"text":"After he bought some linen cloth, Joseph took him down and wrapped him in the linen. Then he laid him in a tomb cut out of the rock and rolled a stone against the entrance to the tomb.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:47","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":15,"verse":47,"text":"Mary Magdalene and Mary the mother of Joses were watching where he was laid.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","chapter":15,"paragraphStarts":[1,2,3,6,13,14,15,16,21,22,24,29,33,35,36,37,40,42],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"Jesus Faces Pilate"},{"beforeVerse":6,"text":"Jesus or Barabbas"},{"beforeVerse":16,"text":"Mocked by the Military"},{"beforeVerse":21,"text":"Crucified Between Two Criminals"},{"beforeVerse":33,"text":"The Death of Jesus"},{"beforeVerse":42,"text":"The Burial of Jesus"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"As "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 27:2","book":"Mat","chapter":27,"verse":2,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 27:11","book":"Mat","chapter":27,"verse":11,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 23:25","book":"Luk","chapter":23,"verse":25,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jn 18:28–38","book":"Jhn","chapter":18,"verse":28,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" soon as it was morning, having held a meeting with the elders, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"3Jn 1","book":"3Jn","chapter":1,"verse":1,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" scribes, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 2:4","book":"Mat","chapter":2,"verse":4,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"text","text":" and the whole Sanhedrin, the chief priests "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 13:9","book":"Mrk","chapter":13,"verse":9,"letter":"g"},{"kind":"text","text":" tied Jesus up, led him away, and handed him over to Pilate. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Tm 6:13","book":"1Ti","chapter":6,"verse":13,"letter":"h"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Mt 27:2","book":"Mat","chapter":27,"verse":2},{"label":"Mt 27:11","book":"Mat","chapter":27,"verse":11},{"label":"Lk 23:25","book":"Luk","chapter":23,"verse":25},{"label":"Jn 18:28–38","book":"Jhn","chapter":18,"verse":28},{"label":"3Jn 1","book":"3Jn","chapter":1,"verse":1},{"label":"Mt 2:4","book":"Mat","chapter":2,"verse":4},{"label":"Mk 13:9","book":"Mrk","chapter":13,"verse":9},{"label":"1Tm 6:13","book":"1Ti","chapter":6,"verse":13}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:2","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"So Pilate asked him, “Are you the king "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 19:38","book":"Luk","chapter":19,"verse":38,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" of the Jews?” "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jn 19:21","book":"Jhn","chapter":19,"verse":21,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" He answered him, “You say so.”"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Lk 19:38","book":"Luk","chapter":19,"verse":38},{"label":"Jn 19:21","book":"Jhn","chapter":19,"verse":21}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:3","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"And the chief priests accused him of many things. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:4","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Pilate "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Tm 6:13","book":"1Ti","chapter":6,"verse":13,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" questioned him again, “Aren’t you going to answer? Look how many things they are accusing you of!” "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Tm 6:13","book":"1Ti","chapter":6,"verse":13}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:5","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"But Jesus still did not answer, and so Pilate was amazed."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:6","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"At "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 27:15–26","book":"Mat","chapter":27,"verse":15,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 23:13–25","book":"Luk","chapter":23,"verse":13,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jn 18:39","book":"Jhn","chapter":18,"verse":39,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" the festival "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 14:1","book":"Mrk","chapter":14,"verse":1,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" Pilate "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Tm 6:13","book":"1Ti","chapter":6,"verse":13,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" used to release for the people a prisoner whom they requested. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Mt 27:15–26","book":"Mat","chapter":27,"verse":15},{"label":"Lk 23:13–25","book":"Luk","chapter":23,"verse":13},{"label":"Jn 18:39","book":"Jhn","chapter":18,"verse":39},{"label":"Mk 14:1","book":"Mrk","chapter":14,"verse":1},{"label":"1Tm 6:13","book":"1Ti","chapter":6,"verse":13}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:7","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"There was one named Barabbas, who was in prison with rebels who had committed murder "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Pr 1:16","book":"Pro","chapter":1,"verse":16,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" during the rebellion. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 23:7","book":"Act","chapter":23,"verse":7,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Pr 1:16","book":"Pro","chapter":1,"verse":16},{"label":"Ac 23:7","book":"Act","chapter":23,"verse":7}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:8","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"The crowd came up and began to ask Pilate to do for them as was his custom. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:9","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Pilate answered them, “Do you want me to release the king "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 19:38","book":"Luk","chapter":19,"verse":38,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" of the Jews "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jn 19:21","book":"Jhn","chapter":19,"verse":21,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" for you?” "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Lk 19:38","book":"Luk","chapter":19,"verse":38},{"label":"Jn 19:21","book":"Jhn","chapter":19,"verse":21}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:10","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"For he knew it was because of envy "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 37:1","book":"Psa","chapter":37,"verse":1,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" that the chief priests had handed him over. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ps 37:1","book":"Psa","chapter":37,"verse":1}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:11","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"But the chief priests stirred up the crowd so that he would release Barabbas to them instead. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:12","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Pilate asked them again, “Then what do you want me to do with the one you call the king of the Jews?”"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:13","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Again they shouted, “Crucify him!”"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:14","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Pilate said to them, “Why? What has he done wrong?”"},{"kind":"text","text":" But they shouted all the more, “Crucify him!”"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:15","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Wanting to satisfy the crowd, Pilate released Barabbas to them; and after having Jesus flogged, he handed him over to be crucified."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:16","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"The "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 27:27–31","book":"Mat","chapter":27,"verse":27,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" soldiers led him away into the palace (that is, the governor’s residence "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jn 18:28","book":"Jhn","chapter":18,"verse":28,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jn 18:33","book":"Jhn","chapter":18,"verse":33,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jn 19:9","book":"Jhn","chapter":19,"verse":9,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 23:35","book":"Act","chapter":23,"verse":35,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Php 1:13","book":"Php","chapter":1,"verse":13,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"text","text":") and called the whole company together. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Mt 27:27–31","book":"Mat","chapter":27,"verse":27},{"label":"Jn 18:28","book":"Jhn","chapter":18,"verse":28},{"label":"Jn 18:33","book":"Jhn","chapter":18,"verse":33},{"label":"Jn 19:9","book":"Jhn","chapter":19,"verse":9},{"label":"Ac 23:35","book":"Act","chapter":23,"verse":35},{"label":"Php 1:13","book":"Php","chapter":1,"verse":13}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:15:17","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"They dressed him in a purple "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 15:20","book":"Mrk","chapter":15,"verse":20,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 16:19","book":"Luk","chapter":16,"verse":19,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rv 18:12","book":"Rev","chapter":18,"verse":12,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" robe, twisted together a crown "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jn 19:2","book":"Jhn","chapter":19,"verse":2,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jn 19:5","book":"Jhn","chapter":19,"verse":5,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rv 12:1","book":"Rev","chapter":12,"verse":1,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"text","text":" of thorns, and put it on him. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Mk 15:20","book":"Mrk","chapter":15,"verse":20},{"label":"Lk 16:19","book":"Luk","chapter":16,"verse":19},{"label":"Rv 18:12","book":"Rev","chapter":18,"verse":12},{